MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience equivalent to the next lower grade level (GS/GG-14) or pay band in the federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing duties such as:
1) Analyzing and mitigating risks to determine acceptable courses of action;
2) Conducting analysis and identifying program issues in order to develop and implement threat reduction actions,
3) Overseeing cyber operations in order to identify threats;
4) Developing annual budget and resource requirements to address shortfalls, mitigate risks, improve performance, and cultivate workforce talent;
5) Updating organizational goals and objectives to keep pace with continually changing intelligence activities, operational environments and the nature of cyber threats. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series
